  <T n="name">0xAF1EFD5F<!--String: "Painting Pets"--></T>
  <U n="notification">
    <L n="ui_responses">
      <U>
        <T n="text">0xA13F0B8C<!--String: "Learn More   NOT USED"--></T>
        <E n="ui_request">SHOW_LESSONS</E>
      </U>
    </L>
  </U>
  <L n="slides">
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InEP04\UI\Tutorial\CAP_Painting_01.png">2f7d0004:00000000:4ce60413c68a1560</T>
      <T n="image_console" p="InEP04\UI\Tutorial_controller\CAP_Painting_01_controller.png">2f7d0004:00000000:860006ec878f4803</T>
      <T n="text">0xF7408A1C<!--String: "Paint Mode can be accessed from a few places: click on the bottom arc menu button from the face or body arc menu, or click on the Paint Mode button at the top of the Coat Color / Pattern catalog."--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InEP04\UI\Tutorial\CAP_Painting_02.png">2f7d0004:00000000:4ce60413c68a1563</T>
      <T n="image_console" p="InEP04\UI\Tutorial_controller\CAP_Painting_02_controller.png">2f7d0004:00000000:beb11898dfc1404e</T>
      <T n="text">0xF7408A1F<!--String: "Start Painting! Just like you can directly push and pull to change the shape of your pet, you can use your mouse cursor as a paint brush to create a hairy masterpiece. Choose from the available color swatches or fine-tune your own color with the color wheel. Click the square to the left of the color wheel to adjust the hue/saturation/brightness values manually."--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InEP04\UI\Tutorial\CAP_Painting_03.png">2f7d0004:00000000:4ce60413c68a1562</T>
      <T n="text">0x5D339D3F<!--String: "Painting is set to paint on both sides of the pet by default, but if you want to go for an asymmetrical look, simply click the mirror paint button. If you want to cover your entire pet with a certain color, use the Fill Color tool."--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InEP04\UI\Tutorial\CAP_Painting_04.png">2f7d0004:00000000:4ce60413c68a1565</T>
      <T n="text">0xF7408A19<!--String: "Choose from a variety of paintbrush shapes and use the Size and Rotation sliders for the exact look you want. Or go a little crazy and play with the Stamps from the Stamps tab. Who said dogs can't be covered in plumbobs?"--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InEP04\UI\Tutorial\CAP_Painting_06.png">2f7d0004:00000000:4ce60413c68a1567</T>
      <T n="image_console" p="InEP04\UI\Tutorial_controller\CAP_Painting_06_controller.png">2f7d0004:00000000:95ac2717cffcdc1a</T>
      <T n="text">0xF7408A18<!--String: "Trying to reach a specific spot? Use the Pose buttons at the top of the screen to access your pet's belly or to get a better look at the top of their head. You can also paint your Pet's nose, inner ears, or paws by clicking the Detail Paint Mode button when you're zoomed in. "--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InEP04\UI\Tutorial\CAP_Painting_05.png">2f7d0004:00000000:4ce60413c68a1564</T>
      <T n="image_console" p="InEP04\UI\Tutorial_controller\CAP_Painting_05_controller.png">2f7d0004:00000000:b07c9bd533959eef</T>
      <T n="text">0xF7408A1B<!--String: "Use the Stencils tab to paint within artist-crafted marking patterns with precision. Play around with the Fill Color tool or paint over the stencil area with multiple colors to get some crazy combinations!"--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InEP04\UI\Tutorial\CAP_Painting_07.png">2f7d0004:00000000:4ce60413c68a1566</T>
      <T n="text">0xF7408A1A<!--String: "When you're done painting, go ahead and click the Back button in the upper left of the paint panel. Or click the Clear All button to start from scratch."--></T>
    </U>
  </L>
